{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Creative tension between people and within individuals is fundamental to social evolution.", "abstract": "David Brooks Op-Ed column submits that creativity is often the result of clashing value systems or traditions combining to create transcendent third thing; holds current widespread disillusion has given rise to creative society, as people are forced to reconcile with institutions that they distrust; says creativity is especially evident in world of B corporations, where people disenchanted with both traditional capitalism and traditional charity seek to synthesize the two.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "21", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "David", "role": "reported", "lastname": "BROOKS", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By DAVID BROOKS", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/07/08/opinion/david-brooks-the-creative-climate.html", "lead_paragraph": "Creative tension between people and within individuals is fundamental to social evolution.", "headline": {"main": "The Creative Climate", "print_headline": "The Creative Climate", "content_kicker": "Op-Ed Columnist", "kicker": "Op-Ed Columnist"}, "_id": "53bb404838f0d847f10f5cc8", "word_count": "802", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2010/09/16/opinion/Brooks_New/Brooks_New-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2010/09/16/opinion/Brooks_New/Brooks_New-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 900, "url": "images/2010/09/16/opinion/Brooks_New/Brooks_New-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2010/09/16/opinion/Brooks_New/Brooks_New-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "900"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2010/09/16/opinion/Brooks_New/Brooks_New-thumbStandard.jpg", "legacy": {"thumbnail": "images/2010/09/16/opinion/Brooks_New